The paper deals with summarizing graph streams, which is a problem related to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of probabilistic graph models and error bounds suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.SI). Additionally, the application areas mentioned (cyber security, social networks, transportation networks) suggest a possible connection to social and information networks (cs.SD).
